properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 23 at 10:29PM AKST until January 25 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow and cold wind chills occuring. Visibility
will be one half mile or less at times. Wind chills to 45 below
occuring. Plan on areas of poor visibilities to create difficult
travel conditions at times. North winds gusting to 35 mph will
cause areas of blowing and drifting snow.

* WHERE...Southeastern Brooks Range near passes.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM Saturday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds gusting to 35 mph will cause areas of
blowing and drifting snow. Cold wind chills as low as 45 below
zero will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to exposed
skin. Travelers should be prepared for large snow drifts and
very cold wind chills.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for blowing snow means periods of
blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The latest road
conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
